Commentary Text: A Russell to Pant, out Caught by Karthik!! What was that, Mr.Pant? We have seen Indian batsmen get out to the bouncer but trust me, this has to be one of weirdest ways of getting out. Lovely bouncer and Pant was stuck on the crease, probably beaten for both pace and bounce. Fails to drop his wrists in time and it flies high off the glove. It's a dolly for the KKR skipper and suddenly, the visitors are right back in this with the twin strikes. The in-form Pant has to go. He has a wry smile on his face as he walks back. Knows that it looked comical. On second viewing, the ball didn't bounce much at all but Pant wasn't looking at the ball in any case. 'Never take your eyes off the ball', they say. Pant c Karthik b A Russell 0(1)

Commentary Text: Chawla to Prithvi Shaw, out Bowled!! Chawla strikes! KKR badly needed this one because this partnership was getting ready to go bonkers. This was the quicker one from Chawla and it skidded through low, Shaw didn't expect it to keep that low and his wild pull across the line didn't help his cause either. Misses it completely and the woodwork is disturbed. Nevertheless, a top quality innings from the young man. He's made a statement here in the IPL. This dismissal might actually worry KKR as they have to chase and it has started to keep low. Prithvi Shaw b Chawla 62(44) [4s-7 6s-2]
